WEBVTT

00:17.640 --> 00:18.910
Save him.

00:20.190 --> 00:21.080
Do what you have to do

00:21.080 --> 00:22.150
as a doctor.

00:23.760 --> 00:25.700
If we have to kill him...

00:27.850 --> 00:29.410
I’ll do my job and kill him.

00:34.650 --> 00:36.610
Don’t save him!

00:36.610 --> 00:39.560
Please just let him die! Please!

00:40.620 --> 00:43.540
Shut her up! Kill her!

00:49.780 --> 00:50.970
He’s in shock due to excessive bleeding.

00:52.160 --> 00:53.400
We have to move him inside.

00:57.350 --> 00:58.700
It’s your call.

00:59.790 --> 01:03.080
You can put your gun down and move him inside

01:03.080 --> 01:06.650
or just let him die here.

01:08.750 --> 01:13.320
I recommend choosing the latter.

01:21.400 --> 01:22.789
Hold tight!

01:24.780 --> 01:26.010
It hurts like hell!

01:27.220 --> 01:29.039
Did you give me any painkillers?

01:36.350 --> 01:37.820
I forgot.

01:37.820 --> 01:39.430
Because I’m not a skilled doctor.

01:47.320 --> 01:48.780
This is Wild Wolf.

01:48.780 --> 01:50.620
Big Boss, Big Boss.

01:50.620 --> 01:51.830
Can you hear me?

01:52.240 --> 01:53.210
Big boss, please answer me.

01:53.210 --> 01:55.020
I think the Korean Army is coming.

01:55.020 --> 01:56.280
Should we gather our side?

01:57.070 --> 01:59.110
If the Korean Army's here,

02:00.210 --> 02:01.900
then we should retreat.

02:01.900 --> 02:02.880
But...

02:05.210 --> 02:06.740
They are not for your guys.

02:08.500 --> 02:10.199
Then we should head back.

02:12.520 --> 02:14.120
You can’t take her.

02:14.120 --> 02:15.370
I removed the bullet

02:15.370 --> 02:18.380
but you’d better get to the hospital first.

02:18.940 --> 02:20.170
What I have done can only make sure that

02:20.170 --> 02:23.660
you won’t die right away.

02:28.680 --> 02:31.280
Patima, when I see you again,

02:31.560 --> 02:35.870
I promise that you will die with that lovely face.

02:36.560 --> 02:38.990
If you’re going to leave,

02:38.990 --> 02:41.260
run as fast as you can

02:42.079 --> 02:44.110
and as far away as you can.

02:45.420 --> 02:48.520
My kindness is up to here.

03:07.920 --> 03:10.620
Did Argus leave the army?

03:11.830 --> 03:14.210
Yes, he’s an arms dealer now.

03:15.890 --> 03:17.930
I bumped into him downtown once.

03:21.920 --> 03:22.780
If we want to get a job

03:22.780 --> 03:23.520
using our special abilities,

03:23.520 --> 03:25.340
it’s either as a mercenary or a criminal.

03:25.340 --> 03:29.130
It’s common for former special forces

03:29.930 --> 03:31.950
who left the brigade to follow money.

03:42.310 --> 03:44.480
Measles and cholera

03:44.480 --> 03:46.170
usually follow natural disasters

03:46.170 --> 03:47.660
and that’s what really happened.

03:48.420 --> 03:51.860
Wow, we saved a world leader, went through an earthquake

03:51.860 --> 03:53.940
and now an epidemic?

03:53.940 --> 03:55.910
That’s why I suggested to run as soon as we got here...

03:58.390 --> 03:59.510
Let’s go.

03:59.760 --> 04:01.510
-Bye.
-This way.

04:01.800 --> 04:03.080
Good boy!

04:03.080 --> 04:04.190
His fever’s down,

04:04.190 --> 04:06.100
but he’s not out of the woods yet.

04:06.100 --> 04:07.880
Some are showing symptoms of pneumonia.

04:10.200 --> 04:11.520
They’re not serious  though.

04:11.860 --> 04:13.090
We can treat measles.

04:13.090 --> 04:14.590
It’s not so terrible.

04:14.590 --> 04:15.880
Go get changed.

04:16.209 --> 04:17.480
Wash the blood off your hands as well.

04:17.820 --> 04:19.010
What’s with the blood?

04:32.180 --> 04:33.240
Save him.

04:34.080 --> 04:34.970
Do what you have to do

04:34.970 --> 04:36.170
as a doctor.

04:38.990 --> 04:40.320
If we have to kill him,

04:40.800 --> 04:42.510
I’ll do my job and kill him.

04:50.550 --> 04:52.409
You know you’re with a dangerous man.

04:53.380 --> 04:55.330
There’s more chance of getting hurt

04:55.330 --> 04:57.040
being around a guy with a gun.

05:07.610 --> 05:08.830
Dr. Kang! Dr. Kang!

05:09.440 --> 05:11.670
That girl who you brought in

05:11.670 --> 05:14.010
said that she’s leaving right now. What should we do?

05:23.120 --> 05:26.180
Eat first. Let’s talk after.

05:27.140 --> 05:28.860
Why did you save him?

05:28.860 --> 05:30.430
You should have just let him die.

05:30.430 --> 05:31.840
You could have been a murderer

05:31.840 --> 05:33.690
If I just let him die.

05:33.690 --> 05:34.900
I saved you from it.

05:34.900 --> 05:37.240
You stopped me from becoming a murderer,

05:37.240 --> 05:39.800
but you can’t stop me from getting killed.

05:40.370 --> 05:41.880
There is an army out there,

05:41.880 --> 05:44.710
so you’ll never get killed.

05:45.390 --> 05:49.050
Army? You want me to trust soldiers?

05:49.050 --> 05:51.409
Have you experienced a war?

05:51.409 --> 05:54.480
Have you seen a soldier in a war?

05:55.320 --> 05:57.140
I didn’t think so.

05:57.140 --> 05:58.880
So get out of my way,

05:58.880 --> 06:00.250
because I’m leaving.

06:01.620 --> 06:03.550
What are you doing?

06:03.550 --> 06:06.710
You can blame me all you want,

06:07.550 --> 06:09.400
but eat first.

06:12.000 --> 06:13.870
And pull yourself together

06:13.870 --> 06:15.230
if you want to run away.

06:18.990 --> 06:20.810
So, keep going.

06:20.810 --> 06:22.490
That’s why we ran.

06:22.490 --> 06:23.480
And when we got there,

06:23.480 --> 06:25.580
half of the power plants were buried underground.

06:25.580 --> 06:27.430
The ground kept cracking everywhere.

06:27.430 --> 06:29.780
A dump truck was crumpled like a beer can.

06:29.780 --> 06:31.290
Patients kept coming in.

06:31.290 --> 06:33.090
Mines were going off everywhere.

06:33.090 --> 06:35.110
It was totally chaos.

06:35.110 --> 06:37.270
What about those who stay there?

06:37.270 --> 06:39.190
Why do they stay if it’s so dangerous?

06:39.650 --> 06:41.640
Honestly speaking, everyone wants to come back,

06:42.110 --> 06:43.760
but there are still patients who need help,

06:43.760 --> 06:45.700
and we are short on doctors.

06:46.270 --> 06:47.600
Staying there a few more days

06:47.600 --> 06:49.350
doesn’t seem like much.

06:49.350 --> 06:51.060
But we felt bad

06:51.060 --> 06:52.390
leaving them behind.

06:55.050 --> 06:56.940
I’m sorry to interrupt you,

06:56.940 --> 06:58.600
but why didn’t Chi Hoon come back?

06:58.600 --> 07:01.020
His name was on the passenger list.

07:01.020 --> 07:03.090
But why wasn’t he on the plane?

07:03.090 --> 07:04.690
Well...

07:04.690 --> 07:05.940
Just before we left,

07:05.940 --> 07:08.200
we had a patient who urgently needed to come back to Korea.

07:08.200 --> 07:09.180
So he gave up his seat.

07:09.730 --> 07:11.310
Oh! Lee Chi Hoon, he’s a real doctor now!

07:11.610 --> 07:13.450
Was it really because of a patient?

07:13.450 --> 07:16.160
He’s not having an affair there or something?

07:16.160 --> 07:19.690
How come he’s not calling me?

07:20.540 --> 07:22.410
Please think about it.

07:22.410 --> 07:24.970
Was there anything suspicious about him?

07:24.970 --> 07:27.270
Come to think of it, he was acting weird.

07:27.270 --> 07:28.600
Not only was he faking illness,

07:28.600 --> 07:30.960
but he seemed to be running away from something.

07:32.520 --> 07:33.690
Who?

07:33.690 --> 07:36.440
That jerk who took Dr. Lee’s seat.

07:36.440 --> 07:38.000
He threw a fit to get a ticket,

07:38.000 --> 07:39.240
but didn’t get on the plane.

07:39.860 --> 07:41.020
They couldn’t find him anywhere,

07:41.020 --> 07:43.520
so they left without him.

07:44.270 --> 07:45.220
Unbelievable!

07:45.220 --> 07:46.920
Then did he get on the plane?

07:46.920 --> 07:47.920
Who?

07:49.190 --> 07:50.290
My soul.

07:54.600 --> 07:58.070
I do like Dr. Song’s witty comments.

07:58.500 --> 07:59.970
He’s such a funny guy.

07:59.970 --> 08:01.090
Ms. Choi.

08:01.440 --> 08:02.480
Yes?

08:04.040 --> 08:05.080
Me too.

08:06.230 --> 08:07.480
Measles are spreading

08:07.480 --> 08:08.890
throughout the refugee camps.

08:08.890 --> 08:11.890
The UN has issued a warning for measles.

08:11.890 --> 08:13.590
I heard it from headquarters.

08:13.910 --> 08:15.520
We have enough MMR vaccines.

08:15.520 --> 08:16.570
Don’t worry.

08:16.570 --> 08:19.420
There are still a dozen children in the village.

08:19.460 --> 08:21.340
Don’t you think I should come along?

08:21.340 --> 08:23.310
Are you really this thick?

08:24.300 --> 08:26.950
Sergeant Seo is in charge of security tomorrow.

08:27.860 --> 08:29.270
This is official, yet private.

08:29.270 --> 08:31.180
Can you, a civilian, stay out of it please?

08:31.180 --> 08:33.520
Unbelievable! How craft you are!

08:33.520 --> 08:35.770
Do you leave early in the morning?

08:36.679 --> 08:38.049
Why are you being nice to me?

08:38.049 --> 08:39.260
I still have a bone to pick with you.

08:39.260 --> 08:41.940
I guess I’m a bigger person than you are.

08:42.789 --> 08:43.860
Be careful.

08:48.240 --> 08:50.610
I can’t pull this sister-in-law card anymore.

08:55.570 --> 08:58.680
Wow, it’s a beautiful day!

08:59.750 --> 09:01.680
Though I like this guy sitting next to me more than that.

09:03.990 --> 09:06.000
Why are you so happy

09:06.000 --> 09:07.530
to carry out a mission with a soldier?

09:08.340 --> 09:09.820
Because I have such high standards.

09:11.220 --> 09:12.770
Are you sure they're high standards?

09:13.870 --> 09:15.620
Don't you look at yourself in the mirror every morning?

09:17.010 --> 09:19.610
If you don't, let me see your face every morning then.

09:19.610 --> 09:21.230
Your incredibly handsome face.

09:25.730 --> 09:29.630
Haven't you ever thought about
doing something else

09:29.630 --> 09:31.310
for a living other than being a soldier?

09:32.170 --> 09:33.760
Are you asking about me?

09:33.760 --> 09:35.230
I'm asking about me.

09:36.890 --> 09:38.650
What do you mean?

09:39.400 --> 09:41.460
This is a dangerous mission

09:41.460 --> 09:43.970
and there are many long gaps of time
when we're apart.

09:45.310 --> 09:49.040
Are you saying these things out of consideration for me?

09:49.400 --> 09:50.930
Because I’m so concerned.

09:51.280 --> 09:53.050
I'm concerned about us.

09:55.550 --> 09:58.480
I feel like I should be
touched by that statement.

10:00.090 --> 10:01.780
but forget it.

10:02.090 --> 10:04.580
I like Sergeant Seo Dae Young the way he is.

10:08.040 --> 10:10.040
The Seo Dae Young I know

10:10.040 --> 10:13.150
is either wearing an army uniform
or wearing nothing.

10:14.320 --> 10:15.370
It's definitely one of those.

10:16.710 --> 10:17.970
Unless I ask you to take it off,

10:17.970 --> 10:19.900
don't you dare take your uniform off
and quit the army.

10:44.540 --> 10:45.650
There seems to be nobody here.

10:47.720 --> 10:49.120
This village is empty.

10:56.380 --> 10:57.320
You know who this guy is.

10:57.320 --> 11:00.010
Former US Army Major Argus.

11:00.010 --> 11:01.580
He's currently an arms dealer.

11:02.020 --> 11:02.870
I heard that

11:02.870 --> 11:04.400
he was part of the operation

11:04.400 --> 11:06.150
that we lost Captain Kim Jin Seok.

11:07.490 --> 11:08.720
Yes, sir.

11:18.380 --> 11:20.880
The CIA has asked us
for our cooperation

11:20.880 --> 11:22.520
through the UN Chief
of the General Staff.

11:22.520 --> 11:25.420
Is this a joint operation to sweep up the illegal arms trade?

11:25.420 --> 11:26.510
No.

11:26.960 --> 11:30.520
This mission isn't about justice. It's about politics.

11:33.330 --> 11:34.760
The number two person in North Uruk

11:34.760 --> 11:36.110
is Colonel Aman.

11:36.110 --> 11:37.710
The United States wants him to start a coup

11:37.710 --> 11:39.730
and establish a pro-America
government in North Uruk.

11:40.760 --> 11:42.320
So they want to provide Aman

11:42.910 --> 11:45.910
a great number of weapons through Argus.

11:52.270 --> 11:55.090
Members of the delta team in US have already taken action.

11:56.000 --> 11:58.060
And I think you know him well.

12:08.590 --> 12:10.280
So until the operation is over,

12:10.280 --> 12:13.410
or in other words, Argus is useful to us,

12:13.410 --> 12:15.200
We don't want any troubles.

12:15.200 --> 12:16.150
This is what they asked for.

12:16.150 --> 12:18.390
We won't strike them first.

12:18.390 --> 12:19.740
but it's our job

12:19.740 --> 12:20.790
to maintain the public security.

12:20.830 --> 12:22.200
Yoo Shi Jin!

12:22.200 --> 12:23.600
Yes, sir!

12:23.600 --> 12:25.870
The commander is giving a direct order

12:25.870 --> 12:27.290
to a mere field commanding officer.

12:27.290 --> 12:28.710
I'm not reporting on the situation here.

12:29.950 --> 12:31.040
I flew here

12:31.040 --> 12:32.380
to stop you from
doing anything unnecessary

12:32.380 --> 12:34.430
and I'm flying back home in 10 minutes.

12:34.830 --> 12:37.480
What I'm saying is I did what I could do.

12:38.150 --> 12:39.530
That's an order.

12:39.530 --> 12:43.560
From this moment on, we're not going to interfere with this.

12:45.840 --> 12:46.830
Yes, sir!

12:47.930 --> 12:49.790
And they said that

12:49.790 --> 12:51.660
those kids from the ghost village

12:51.660 --> 12:54.210
were moved to an orphanage in the city.

12:54.250 --> 12:55.850
But something smells fishy.

12:59.950 --> 13:01.410
Sir.

13:03.970 --> 13:05.700
As of now,

13:06.590 --> 13:10.170
we're taking our hands off of anything that involves Argus.

13:12.680 --> 13:14.760
I went back from headquarters.

13:16.930 --> 13:19.600
What I'm going to tell you from this moment on

13:20.330 --> 13:22.670
is strictly confidential.

13:50.460 --> 13:52.520
I thought you might need something sweet.

13:53.160 --> 13:55.600
This is my last one,
but I'm giving it to you.

14:01.460 --> 14:02.540
Thank you.

14:03.300 --> 14:04.410
We can share.

14:04.850 --> 14:06.110
Too many calories.

14:06.110 --> 14:08.190
Drink it. Think of it as a tonic.

14:14.300 --> 14:16.830
What happened to the kids back in the ghost village?

14:16.830 --> 14:18.200
I haven't seen Lieutenant Yoon yet.

14:19.210 --> 14:20.450
It's all taken care of.

14:21.950 --> 14:23.600
The Uruk government will move them to a safe place

14:23.650 --> 14:24.420
and protect them.

14:24.420 --> 14:25.600
That's nice.

14:26.100 --> 14:27.600
The children we brought to the medical zone

14:27.600 --> 14:30.180
seem to be recovering well since we started treatment right away.

14:30.610 --> 14:32.430
That's why you were so busy.

14:32.620 --> 14:34.520
Busy enough that you had no time to tie your hair back.

14:37.510 --> 14:38.900
Hold this for a second.

14:40.760 --> 14:41.760
You usually do something weird

14:41.760 --> 14:42.990
whenever you ask me to hold something.

14:44.940 --> 14:47.430
No! You can't! I haven't washed my hair today.

14:47.990 --> 14:50.070
Why? You didn't have mineral water?

14:51.060 --> 14:52.110
Why are you pretending that

14:52.110 --> 14:53.310
you wash your hair that often?

14:53.310 --> 14:54.660
That's not true.

14:55.030 --> 14:56.950
When am I going to meet the real Dr. Kang?

15:02.690 --> 15:04.230
I can do it myself.

15:05.330 --> 15:06.880
When you're in a relationship,

15:06.930 --> 15:09.680
your boyfriend usually does things that you can do yourself.

15:10.360 --> 15:12.130
I'll do the same for you later.

15:12.910 --> 15:15.750
I'll do things for you
that you can do yourself.

15:17.240 --> 15:18.520
Make sure to keep that promise.

15:31.400 --> 15:32.510
This is No.B housemaster.

15:32.560 --> 15:35.760
The medicine and personal packages from Korea are coming.

15:36.180 --> 15:37.530
Oh! Packages! Packages!

15:39.880 --> 15:42.420
Are you ditching me for packages?

15:44.290 --> 15:45.070
Packages or me?

15:45.070 --> 15:46.580
- Of course I'd choose you.

15:52.290 --> 15:53.870
These are from Dr. Pyo.

15:54.230 --> 15:57.210
I know I can count on her.

15:59.240 --> 16:00.510
The smell of Korea.

16:03.240 --> 16:04.400
The smell of a box from Korea.

16:07.780 --> 16:09.240
I'll deliver this one to him.

16:09.990 --> 16:11.560
His sister is so sweet.

16:18.130 --> 16:19.190
Is there anything for you?

16:19.190 --> 16:19.940
Mind your own business.

16:19.940 --> 16:21.000
Why are you asking about mine?

16:21.000 --> 16:23.030
Surprisingly, something came for you.

16:25.430 --> 16:26.490
Who sent it to you?

16:29.010 --> 16:29.900
I did.

16:38.630 --> 16:39.550
These are for you.

16:39.950 --> 16:41.870
Size 240 mm, right?

16:45.080 --> 16:46.660
Dr. Song.

16:48.770 --> 16:50.440
Don't thank me.

16:50.440 --> 16:52.310
I'm a size 230 mm.

16:53.530 --> 16:57.050
Never mind! No one will notice.

16:57.590 --> 16:59.810
I will.

17:17.210 --> 17:19.200
Sergeant Seo, you have a package

17:19.200 --> 17:20.180
from Shin Ji Yeong.

17:20.180 --> 17:22.829
Where are you right now?

17:24.400 --> 17:25.970
Where are you right now?

17:27.880 --> 17:30.870
I’m at camp restaurant, should I wait for you?

17:44.620 --> 17:45.840
Run fast.

17:56.290 --> 17:57.240
Yes, sir.

17:57.850 --> 17:58.920
Yes, sir.

18:00.640 --> 18:01.690
Yes, sir.

18:11.550 --> 18:12.140
You startled me!

18:12.140 --> 18:13.670
I must find out what's in here.

18:15.300 --> 18:17.800
"Dae Young, hang in there. Heart."

18:18.460 --> 18:20.780
"I miss you, Dae Young. Heart."

18:21.830 --> 18:22.970
Hey.

18:22.970 --> 18:24.450
Does Sergeant Seo have a sister?

18:24.930 --> 18:26.310
He's the only child!

18:26.310 --> 18:27.910
That's probably not my fault.

18:30.810 --> 18:31.800
Can you do that?

18:43.630 --> 18:44.850
Would you look at this?

18:44.850 --> 18:47.770
What is it? Why is Yoo Shi Jin here?

18:50.950 --> 18:53.210
"The day I met Shi Jin."

18:53.210 --> 18:55.270
"I'm sending our memories."

18:56.250 --> 18:57.720
How dare they!

18:58.080 --> 19:00.640
Lieutenant Yoon, get me a gun.

19:03.220 --> 19:03.870
It's not what you think.

19:03.870 --> 19:04.910
It's not what you think at all.

19:07.880 --> 19:08.990
It's not what we think?

19:10.630 --> 19:14.220
You two look so chummy with these girls. But it isn't what it looks like?

19:14.220 --> 19:16.040
I see your brightest smile

19:16.040 --> 19:17.380
in this picture.

19:17.380 --> 19:18.870
I'm not smiling.

19:19.220 --> 19:20.240
It looks like I'm smiling,

19:20.240 --> 19:21.700
but I'm not.

19:22.010 --> 19:23.170
Am I right?

19:23.170 --> 19:24.580
She's my cousin.

19:24.580 --> 19:25.490
You know that

19:25.490 --> 19:26.900
my cousin is a flight attendant.

19:26.900 --> 19:27.450
Right.

19:27.450 --> 19:30.110
Your cousin sent you a package

19:30.110 --> 19:31.790
and you two came here together.

19:31.790 --> 19:33.850
Because they all had fun together.

19:36.310 --> 19:38.290
Which of the two is your cousin?

19:38.290 --> 19:39.020
Huh?

19:39.020 --> 19:40.240
Answer me at the same time.

19:40.240 --> 19:42.600
Sergeant Seo, left or right?

19:42.600 --> 19:43.180
One, two, three!

19:43.180 --> 19:44.260
- Right.
- Left.

19:47.350 --> 19:48.980
- Left.
- Right.

19:52.720 --> 19:55.220
I tried to set someone up with Captain Yoo.

19:55.220 --> 19:56.900
Nothing more, nothing less.

19:59.910 --> 20:01.710
Are you ditching your fellow soldier?

20:01.710 --> 20:02.880
Yes, sir!

20:04.170 --> 20:06.420
I guess you've been in contact with her since you came to Uruk.

20:06.420 --> 20:07.960
She knows your address here.

20:08.910 --> 20:10.340
Haven’t you?

20:10.610 --> 20:12.850
Why did you do that, Sergeant Seo?

20:13.270 --> 20:15.350
I don't understand this guy.

20:15.950 --> 20:18.170
I just taught him
a very important lesson.

20:18.350 --> 20:19.370
Didn't I do a good job?

20:19.370 --> 20:20.460
That's enough.

20:20.780 --> 20:21.670
Come with me.

20:22.750 --> 20:23.680
Yes. Lead the way.

20:23.680 --> 20:24.830
Where are you going?

20:27.680 --> 20:29.120
I thought she meant me.

20:29.550 --> 20:31.430
I'm so used to following orders.

20:32.360 --> 20:34.170
Why don't you go?

20:35.300 --> 20:37.250
I want to be with my fellow soldier.

20:41.740 --> 20:42.710
Sir!

20:45.420 --> 20:47.180
I hope you don't get the wrong idea.

20:47.410 --> 20:48.300
It is a thing of the past.

20:48.300 --> 20:51.180
Do not be ridiculous.

20:52.170 --> 20:53.830
Did this come from the past?

20:54.780 --> 20:56.030
It came from Seoul.

20:58.240 --> 21:01.370
I was right, wasn't I? I knew it was a blind date.

21:01.370 --> 21:02.630
He’s the son of Corporal Park of bravo team.

21:02.630 --> 21:04.100
It was the day at Corporal Park's son's first birthday party.

21:04.100 --> 21:04.820
The night

21:04.820 --> 21:06.090
they suddenly disappeared.

21:09.640 --> 21:11.690
They said that one of their high school friend’s father passed away.

21:12.300 --> 21:15.600
They didn't go to the same high school,
so it didn't make sense.

21:15.600 --> 21:17.900
They couldn't even fool us.

21:17.900 --> 21:20.200
They were dressed
quite nicely on that day.

21:20.200 --> 21:22.610
I thought they were hosting the first birthday party.

21:25.690 --> 21:27.610
Is this why you've been avoiding me?

21:27.810 --> 21:28.960
I thought my father

21:29.000 --> 21:29.680
was the obstacle between us.

21:29.680 --> 21:31.410
Your father was the obstacle.

21:31.410 --> 21:33.300
What did you just say?

21:34.690 --> 21:36.050
What did I just say?

21:36.050 --> 21:38.470
Enough. How far did you two go?

21:38.470 --> 21:40.200
To the Konkuk University Station.

21:40.680 --> 21:43.380
That is not what I'm asking.

21:43.380 --> 21:45.160
How far did you go with her?

21:45.160 --> 21:46.590
Did you share physical contact with her?

21:46.590 --> 21:48.530
No, I did not.

21:48.530 --> 21:50.680
It was very innocent.
We just

21:51.090 --> 21:52.160
had coffee together.

21:52.520 --> 21:53.770
What a gentleman!

21:53.770 --> 21:55.200
I am flattered.

21:55.200 --> 21:57.650
You had tea with a girl
once in a while.

21:57.650 --> 21:59.090
When we were apart,

21:59.090 --> 22:00.100
you looked so heartbroken

22:00.100 --> 22:02.190
and pathetic

22:02.190 --> 22:04.240
I felt bad.

22:04.240 --> 22:06.930
I didn't know you would get over it so quickly.

22:07.390 --> 22:08.710
I had a hard time.

22:09.380 --> 22:12.450
Besides, I followed
Sergeant Seo out of friendship.

22:12.450 --> 22:13.710
I was forced to.

22:13.710 --> 22:15.180
Out of friendship, my butt.

22:15.940 --> 22:17.340
You looked so happy

22:17.340 --> 22:20.600
that you didn't know
what to do with yourself rather than not knowing what to do.

22:20.600 --> 22:23.180
I think you got the wrong idea because you only got a glance.

22:23.180 --> 22:26.310
I had no facial expression at all.

22:26.310 --> 22:28.120
I drank tea with this face.

22:28.510 --> 22:30.110
How do I know

22:30.110 --> 22:32.530
you didn't take them
for a drive as well as a cup of tea?

22:32.530 --> 22:33.940
I did not take them for a drive.

22:35.820 --> 22:37.470
You are at risk of making things worse
if you are lying to me.

22:41.250 --> 22:43.030
We took them for a drive.

22:43.700 --> 22:46.930
It was not my car. It was Captain Yoo's.

22:47.500 --> 22:52.210
I really do not understand why he even drove his car.

22:52.920 --> 22:54.770
Do you expect me to believe that?

22:54.770 --> 22:56.630
I want you to forget it.

22:56.630 --> 22:58.960
I do not even remember their names.

22:59.980 --> 23:01.480
Right. You don't even remember their names

23:01.480 --> 23:04.920
but you kept running out of breath
when you heard the name Shin Ji Yeong.

23:05.810 --> 23:06.590
It was not me.

23:06.890 --> 23:08.830
Geeze. This is so frustrating!

23:11.830 --> 23:13.370
This person saved you.

23:13.370 --> 23:15.220
Who is that? It that a guy?

23:15.680 --> 23:17.640
Do you really think you can ask me that at the moment?

23:18.460 --> 23:20.040
Does it matter if it's a girl or a guy?

23:20.040 --> 23:20.930
If it's a girl, I'll buy her dinner.

23:20.930 --> 23:22.270
If it's a guy, I'll buy him a drink.

23:24.050 --> 23:25.330
I'm so thankful.

23:27.860 --> 23:30.520
It's Mr. Han from my hospital! What?

23:34.600 --> 23:36.570
It's Mr. Han from my hospital! What?

23:40.330 --> 23:41.620
Hello!

23:41.620 --> 23:44.490
shouldn't you call me back

23:44.490 --> 23:46.400
and thank me

23:46.400 --> 23:48.070
or something?

23:48.070 --> 23:50.870
I'm sorry. I've been so busy that I haven't even opened it.

23:50.870 --> 23:53.980
What do you mean, busy?

23:53.980 --> 23:56.310
Because you're too busy dating?

23:56.980 --> 23:57.950
How did you know?

23:57.950 --> 24:00.240
Because I heard it from someone.

24:00.240 --> 24:02.120
I heard you two argued today.

24:02.420 --> 24:03.830
How did you know that?

24:03.830 --> 24:05.510
I guess you're really dating him.

24:05.510 --> 24:08.580
It’s true that you are fall in love.

24:09.400 --> 24:10.300
You...are so hateful.

24:10.300 --> 24:12.120
Hold on. Dr. Jang wants to talk to you.

24:14.640 --> 24:17.690
Mo Yeon, it's me, Dr. Jang.

24:18.540 --> 24:20.070
Is everyone lying to me that

24:20.070 --> 24:22.020
Chi Hoon's alive even though he's dead?

24:22.920 --> 24:24.240
What do you mean?

24:24.240 --> 24:26.220
You haven't talked to him yet?

24:26.220 --> 24:27.870
Yes.

24:27.870 --> 24:31.210
Is he going to divorce
his pregnant fiancée?

24:31.210 --> 24:32.920
What a jerk!

24:32.920 --> 24:35.510
Hang in there. He's probably making rounds now.

24:48.280 --> 24:51.450
It's a painkiller. It'll sting a little.

24:53.510 --> 24:54.700
Forget it.

24:55.520 --> 24:57.540
Why don't you leave?

24:57.540 --> 24:59.430
Not seeing your face
is enough of a painkiller.

25:04.290 --> 25:05.850
Don't touch me.

25:06.570 --> 25:09.110
How do I know that you won't hurt me?

25:09.110 --> 25:11.000
If you were me, would you let the person as you treat you?

25:12.080 --> 25:14.110
It probably bugs you
that I'm still alive.

25:17.250 --> 25:18.500
Didn't you hear what I said?

25:19.000 --> 25:21.710
I said go! I won't get the painkiller.

25:28.100 --> 25:29.610
Please save me.

25:34.780 --> 25:40.140
Please... get me out of here.

25:42.080 --> 25:44.600
I was too scared to do so.

25:45.010 --> 25:47.800
I understand how you feel.

25:49.720 --> 25:53.760
I wasn't a doctor in that moment.

25:56.620 --> 25:58.150
I'm sorry

25:59.740 --> 26:02.430
that I ran away by myself.

26:07.140 --> 26:08.880
You're so selfish.

26:09.380 --> 26:12.300
You're saying these things

26:12.890 --> 26:15.750
so you can get the guilt off your chest. Is that right?

26:17.010 --> 26:18.470
If that were true,

26:18.470 --> 26:19.730
I would have done so earlier.

26:21.110 --> 26:26.840
I just... don't know what to do.

26:27.800 --> 26:29.570
Please let me know.

26:30.080 --> 26:31.830
I'll do whatever you ask me.

26:34.280 --> 26:36.720
No matter how much I think about it,

26:36.950 --> 26:40.520
I have no one else to talk to...

26:40.690 --> 26:42.780
except you.

26:42.780 --> 26:44.900
It doesn't matter. Don't expect anything from me.

26:45.550 --> 26:47.680
You didn't hold my hand.

26:48.530 --> 26:50.380
You didn't save me!

26:53.090 --> 26:55.170
Don't try to reach out to me.

26:55.830 --> 26:58.540
I'm not going to take your hand.

27:06.820 --> 27:09.480
I'm going to tell Dr. Song.

27:10.510 --> 27:12.950
So make sure you get this shot. You're very sick.

27:30.980 --> 27:33.010
Hello, Lee Chi Hoon, where are you?

27:33.440 --> 27:34.770
Why are you not in medical zone?

27:35.840 --> 27:37.210
While I’m talking,

27:50.030 --> 27:51.950
you're very sick.

27:57.570 --> 27:58.840
When did you get here?

28:00.220 --> 28:02.070
Are you here alone?

28:03.870 --> 28:05.930
Why are you walking around by yourself?

28:05.930 --> 28:08.100
It's dangerous.

28:14.950 --> 28:17.090
Why are you so sick?

28:29.340 --> 28:31.220
Where the heck is that idiot hiding?

28:33.130 --> 28:35.110
Ms. Ha, Dr. Song, Dr. Kang.

28:35.110 --> 28:37.400
This is pharmaceutical warehouse. Please come here quickly.

28:37.400 --> 28:38.350
Geeze.

28:48.140 --> 28:51.010
The lock's broken. What's missing?

28:51.010 --> 28:54.190
Narcotic analgesics. They're all gone.

28:54.190 --> 28:55.480
Codein, morphine, fentanyl,

28:55.480 --> 28:57.410
levorphanol. Everything.

28:57.410 --> 28:59.170
When was the last time you checked it?

28:59.170 --> 29:00.620
11:00 a.m.

29:00.620 --> 29:03.080
There were no strangers and no missing patients.

29:03.080 --> 29:04.620
What happened?

29:06.540 --> 29:07.970
There are no missing patients,

29:07.970 --> 29:09.590
but there's a missing girl.

29:10.170 --> 29:11.450
This is the medical zone.

29:11.450 --> 29:13.680
Has anyone seen Fatima today?

29:15.350 --> 29:17.440
Tommy? It's me.

29:17.440 --> 29:19.990
I stole the pills that you told me to.

29:19.990 --> 29:21.880
Where should I bring them?

29:22.970 --> 29:25.380
Okay. Miss you a lot.

29:25.380 --> 29:27.430
We should run away after selling this.

29:27.470 --> 29:28.970
I love you, Tommy.

29:30.360 --> 29:32.070
There's no reason why
Fatima would be here.

29:33.100 --> 29:34.280
I can gather intelligence here.

29:38.270 --> 29:39.550
How is everything?

29:39.550 --> 29:42.170
Looks like you need something more than my welcome.

29:42.170 --> 29:43.330
What do you need?

29:44.890 --> 29:46.100
Information.

29:47.740 --> 29:51.000
A 15-year-old girl in a red dress.

29:51.450 --> 29:53.440
She's selling narcotics.

29:53.440 --> 29:55.140
I kept telling you that

29:55.140 --> 29:56.120
we sell everything here

29:56.120 --> 29:59.750
but women and information.

30:01.510 --> 30:02.510
You don't have to,

30:02.510 --> 30:05.940
but there must be
someone else who could.

30:08.030 --> 30:11.420
Hey. Please help us. She's only 15 years old.

30:12.180 --> 30:14.670
We need to find her

30:14.670 --> 30:16.310
before someone else does.

30:22.410 --> 30:25.390
Where's a black market that you can get narcotics?

30:46.820 --> 30:47.890
It should be around here.

30:48.860 --> 30:50.020
How can we find her here?

30:50.670 --> 30:51.880
Do we have to search
every nook and cranny?

30:53.710 --> 30:54.710
Over there!

31:07.080 --> 31:10.010
Son of a bitch! Were you lying to me the whole time?

31:10.010 --> 31:14.290
No! Fatima, no! You trusted me too much.

31:14.670 --> 31:17.140
Follow me before I beat you harder.

31:18.470 --> 31:19.930
Bitch! Do you want to die?

31:19.930 --> 31:21.670
Stop it! Don't hit her!

31:23.600 --> 31:25.860
Isn't he a soldier? Why is he here?

31:25.860 --> 31:28.560
Don't worry. We've got more weapons than him.

31:34.320 --> 31:36.020
I don't know who you guys are looking for.

31:36.020 --> 31:37.830
I hope it's not us.

31:38.190 --> 31:39.490
Guns again?

31:39.490 --> 31:41.820
Why does everyone
have a gun in this country?

31:42.220 --> 31:43.190
Because you don't consult me

31:43.190 --> 31:44.440
before you act.

31:44.760 --> 31:45.820
If we were any later,

31:45.820 --> 31:47.470
Fatima could have been beaten up worse.

31:47.470 --> 31:49.950
Good job. We're about to be shot,

31:49.950 --> 31:51.320
but Fatima is safe.

31:51.320 --> 31:52.990
What the hell are they talking about?

31:52.990 --> 31:54.540
Who cares?

31:54.540 --> 31:57.700
Put your gun down
if you don't want to die.

31:58.710 --> 32:00.220
What should we do?

32:00.220 --> 32:01.980
I'm not all out of ideas.

32:02.370 --> 32:03.910
Seven guns.

32:03.910 --> 32:05.820
You take the right,

32:05.820 --> 32:07.920
and I'll take the left.

32:08.420 --> 32:09.520
Damn it.

32:09.890 --> 32:11.130
Don't be scared!

32:12.710 --> 32:13.760
Okay.

32:15.030 --> 32:16.440
Let's make a deal.

32:17.410 --> 32:21.340
I'll drop my weapon. Let the girls go.

32:21.340 --> 32:23.020
What the hell are you talking about?

32:23.810 --> 32:28.320
You'll put your gun down, and girls, get on your knees now.

32:31.770 --> 32:33.050
I thought he'd go for it.

32:33.050 --> 32:34.310
Are you kidding me?

32:34.310 --> 32:36.130
Okay, I'm done joking around.

32:36.960 --> 32:38.300
Listen to me carefully.

32:39.410 --> 32:42.370
If I say "now," run as fast as you can

32:42.370 --> 32:44.230
and wait for me
in the front with the car.

32:44.620 --> 32:45.930
I just need five minutes.

32:46.520 --> 32:48.530
If I don't come out after the five minute mark,

32:49.370 --> 32:50.660
go without me.

32:50.660 --> 32:51.970
That is how you can help me.

32:51.970 --> 32:53.100
You understand, don't you?

32:55.980 --> 32:58.200
What does that bastard keep saying?

32:58.460 --> 33:01.340
Shut up and drop your weapon!

33:04.140 --> 33:05.150
Okay.

33:06.770 --> 33:08.240
I will. I'll put it down.

33:11.140 --> 33:12.170
Right here?

33:12.170 --> 33:13.220
Is this spot okay with you?

33:17.010 --> 33:20.200
You know what? I can't use this gun.

33:21.120 --> 33:22.670
If I use this gun,

33:23.430 --> 33:25.140
I need to write a report.

33:25.650 --> 33:27.220
So...

33:28.380 --> 33:29.560
Let me use yours.

33:30.920 --> 33:32.090
Now!

34:18.190 --> 34:19.699
It's been over five minutes. Why hasn’t he come?

34:21.600 --> 34:22.639
Geeze! I don't care.

34:55.340 --> 34:57.820
Get on the car!
Fatima! Come on! Quick!

35:08.760 --> 35:10.260
Wow! This is crazy!

35:11.580 --> 35:15.050
No one's following us, right?

35:16.060 --> 35:17.950
We did it! How exciting!

35:17.950 --> 35:19.360
Is this why you became a soldier?

35:21.010 --> 35:23.050
I defeated the bad guys!

35:23.050 --> 35:25.030
You know you almost defeated me, right?

35:25.030 --> 35:26.720
I knew you'd get out of the way.

35:26.720 --> 35:28.510
I took that into consideration as well.

35:29.540 --> 35:33.130
How did she attend medical school
with a brain like that?

35:48.010 --> 35:49.220
What's wrong with the car?

35:51.030 --> 35:52.310
Why wouldn't you know?

35:52.310 --> 35:53.590
Given the way you were driving,

35:55.340 --> 35:57.760
this is the third car
That you’ve  destroyed.

36:19.340 --> 36:21.770
You need to leave the army.

36:22.810 --> 36:24.130
I want you to learn the business

36:25.130 --> 36:27.680
in the company my family owns.

36:27.820 --> 36:29.810
Think about it
until you finish your mission here

36:30.210 --> 36:32.940
and make a decision
before you return to Korea.

36:42.050 --> 36:44.000
You're so stubborn.

36:44.610 --> 36:45.340
I thought I told you to stay in the safe zone

36:45.340 --> 36:48.290
because it was too dangerous.

36:52.460 --> 36:53.820
The safe zone is boring.

36:55.640 --> 36:57.190
Take two steps to the left

36:57.540 --> 36:58.910
and face me.

37:02.420 --> 37:03.560
How dare you

37:03.560 --> 37:05.490
ignore an order
from your superior?

37:06.150 --> 37:08.290
Look at me.

37:14.320 --> 37:15.830
One step forward.

37:23.670 --> 37:25.750
What do you think you're doing?

37:25.750 --> 37:27.410
I'm not trying to make up.

37:28.130 --> 37:29.440
I'm making physical contact.

37:30.150 --> 37:31.200
The boys are watching.

37:31.200 --> 37:32.460
There aren't any boys here.

37:32.460 --> 37:34.010
Do you realize this is abuse?

37:34.010 --> 37:35.390
Why?

37:35.390 --> 37:38.230
Is it considered abuse
because I'm not a flight attendant?

37:43.250 --> 37:45.080
Because it's coming from Lieutenant Yoon Myung Joo.

37:49.400 --> 37:50.600
The boys are watching.

37:52.970 --> 37:54.670
I can beat them all.

38:07.270 --> 38:08.340
This is Big Boss.

38:08.340 --> 38:09.210
We’re now at downtown,

38:09.210 --> 38:11.670
Which is 15km far away from military camp.

38:11.670 --> 38:12.970
Our car was broken.

38:12.970 --> 38:14.740
Please contact me when is close.

38:18.280 --> 38:19.660
I have to get this.

38:20.330 --> 38:21.850
I can't beat this guy.

38:21.850 --> 38:23.780
He doesn't ever help.

38:25.520 --> 38:26.660
This is Wild Wolf.

38:26.940 --> 38:29.130
We're getting rid of land mines near the ghost village.

38:29.130 --> 38:30.240
What happened?

38:30.990 --> 38:33.810
Why are you always stranded on the road?

38:33.810 --> 38:35.530
Why?

38:35.530 --> 38:36.950
Can you send someone over?

38:37.950 --> 38:40.200
Got it. I will send Corporal Gong.

38:51.050 --> 38:52.820
How did she know

38:52.820 --> 38:56.150
and why did she only take narcotic analgesics?

38:56.600 --> 39:00.320
I guess she learned what can get her more money than others.

39:00.740 --> 39:03.030
Disinfectant, antibiotics,

39:03.030 --> 39:05.020
and vaccines which can save people's lives,

39:05.020 --> 39:06.950
are usually cheap.

39:07.490 --> 39:10.430
It would have been better if she learned about those first.

39:13.750 --> 39:16.230
What can I say in English

39:16.730 --> 39:18.320
to make her realize what she has done  wrong?

39:20.590 --> 39:22.310
I guess she already does.

39:25.010 --> 39:28.340
From now on, you do whatever I say.

39:28.510 --> 39:31.590
You have no choice.
Go back to school first.

39:31.590 --> 39:32.980
It’s none of your business.

39:33.020 --> 39:33.980
Why?

39:33.980 --> 39:35.690
I saved your life.

39:36.520 --> 39:38.360
And don't talk back. If you talk back,

39:38.360 --> 39:39.950
I have to keep talking
in my broken English!

39:40.200 --> 39:42.580
I don't like repeating myself, okay? In any case...

39:44.230 --> 39:47.970
I'll pay for your tuition, so finish school first.

39:48.460 --> 39:50.350
Of course it's not free.

39:50.350 --> 39:54.560
I'm just lending it to you, so pay back later.

39:54.560 --> 39:55.580
Okay?

39:59.220 --> 40:01.630
Do you think
she understood everything I said?

40:01.630 --> 40:03.370
Especially the part that it isn't free.

40:03.370 --> 40:04.450
I think she heard that clear.

40:04.450 --> 40:06.420
I particularly stressed that part.

40:06.890 --> 40:09.640
I made a promise.

40:16.510 --> 40:17.810
Phew! I didn't wash it.

40:30.500 --> 40:31.620
What are you doing?

40:32.740 --> 40:35.450
I'm drying my hair.
This fan works the best.

40:36.430 --> 40:38.180
You finally washed your hair.

40:39.460 --> 40:40.930
Did you really wash it?

40:41.320 --> 40:42.460
Did you have enough water?

40:42.900 --> 40:43.900
Go to bed..

40:46.140 --> 40:48.170
Wouldn't it be a waste
to spend tonight on sleep?

40:49.980 --> 40:51.120
Want a bowl of ramen?

40:51.920 --> 40:53.240
What's this?

40:53.240 --> 40:56.210
What's with this R-rated line?

40:58.160 --> 41:00.430
I'm genuinely trying to entice you here.

41:01.540 --> 41:02.670
Hum.

41:02.670 --> 41:03.670
Deal!

41:06.420 --> 41:07.390
Sir!

41:07.390 --> 41:08.580
The water's already boiling.

41:08.580 --> 41:10.240
Two steaming bowls of ramen.

41:11.360 --> 41:12.180
Yes, sir!

41:15.380 --> 41:17.470
What about the car? Can it be fixed?

41:18.880 --> 41:20.670
We don't know yet.

41:20.670 --> 41:22.480
You broke Daniel's car

41:22.530 --> 41:23.680
and this one today.

41:23.680 --> 41:25.070
And her tuition?

41:25.720 --> 41:28.980
Are you really going
to support her tuition?

41:29.530 --> 41:30.380
Why?

41:30.380 --> 41:32.190
I guess you make a lot of money.

41:33.950 --> 41:36.000
Lending a hand in someone's life

41:36.680 --> 41:38.820
is a huge responsibility.

41:39.680 --> 41:40.640
I just do what I can

41:40.640 --> 41:42.430
within my power.

41:42.720 --> 41:44.380
Even if it messes everything up.

41:46.860 --> 41:48.340
You know who said that, right?

41:49.700 --> 41:51.680
See? I can easily forget things.

41:51.680 --> 41:54.560
You can't help everyone you meet here.

41:54.560 --> 41:56.160
That's not going to change the world.

41:56.160 --> 41:58.080
I know I can't change the world.

41:58.920 --> 42:00.880
But Fatima's life may change.

42:01.580 --> 42:03.130
That means Fatima's world

42:03.130 --> 42:05.200
will change.

42:05.520 --> 42:06.930
That's enough then.

42:08.160 --> 42:09.060
You told me you're not

42:09.060 --> 42:09.940
that kind of doctor.

42:09.940 --> 42:12.160
You told me that I was
that kind of doctor.

42:13.300 --> 42:15.270
How can you be so charming so often these days?

42:16.120 --> 42:17.450
I've already fallen for you.

42:19.580 --> 42:21.280
I have lots of debt.

42:21.620 --> 42:24.130
If you have lots of debt, it's easy to get dumped.

42:27.910 --> 42:29.790
Thank you for saving my life today.

42:34.130 --> 42:35.750
Two steaming bowls of ramen.

42:35.750 --> 42:39.050
-Coming up! -Thank you.

42:39.440 --> 42:41.220
Thank you.

42:43.400 --> 42:45.950
Ah, why now of all times?

42:45.950 --> 42:49.460
What’s the matter? Do you have a lantern?

42:49.460 --> 42:50.800
The noodles will get soggy.

42:52.530 --> 42:55.070
Should we eat like soldiers out in the field?

42:56.790 --> 42:59.920
Wow! I can see it now.

42:59.920 --> 43:02.340
I can do fun things because my boyfriend's a special forces officer.

43:04.930 --> 43:06.510
I think you're soldier material.

43:07.090 --> 43:08.150
Why don't you just

43:08.150 --> 43:09.120
join the army?

43:09.120 --> 43:11.000
What else can I do if I join the army?

43:11.570 --> 43:13.530
Right! Shall we play soccer?

43:13.920 --> 43:17.000
When I go back to Korea, I'll tell my friends about it.

43:18.110 --> 43:19.980
Okay. Bottoms up!

43:21.420 --> 43:23.000
Bottoms up! Eat!

43:29.620 --> 43:31.190
He’s finally coming out.

43:32.790 --> 43:34.760
I only drank water to prevent this. Ah!

44:19.970 --> 44:21.050
Okay.

44:59.740 --> 45:01.490
Geeze!

45:01.490 --> 45:03.040
It stinks. Geeze!

45:20.130 --> 45:22.040
Manager Jin got caught at the airport?

45:22.040 --> 45:24.800
Yes, he was holding a fake passport.

45:25.120 --> 45:27.620
But the Mouru Police took him

45:27.620 --> 45:29.260
instead of the American army or Interpol.

45:29.410 --> 45:30.390
The Korean embassy

45:30.390 --> 45:32.520
has requested to check his identity.

45:33.490 --> 45:35.090
Someone wants to get his hands on Mr. Jin

45:35.090 --> 45:38.020
while bribing the Mouru police chief.

45:38.020 --> 45:39.520
Is it because of the diamonds?

45:40.410 --> 45:42.490
Seriously, how much are these diamonds

45:42.490 --> 45:44.770
worth?

45:44.770 --> 45:46.080
Diamonds?

45:48.790 --> 45:50.000
Elaborate.

45:50.000 --> 45:52.490
On the day he came by the supply truck,

45:52.670 --> 45:54.940
I saw him putting them in the safe box.

46:07.210 --> 46:08.310
Supply truck?

46:09.600 --> 46:10.480
The one that crosses the border?

46:10.480 --> 46:11.530
Yes.

46:11.530 --> 46:14.610
Mr. Jin made sure that he checked the supplies on the truck.

46:16.090 --> 46:18.180
He had blood on his pants one day.

46:20.990 --> 46:24.420
Ah, those diamonds were real?

46:25.200 --> 46:26.320
That jerk!

46:26.980 --> 46:28.150
I knew he was up to no good.

46:28.150 --> 46:29.620
It’s suspicious. Why are you telling me this now?

46:29.620 --> 46:32.210
I was busy going through a near-death experience, you know.

46:32.780 --> 46:33.830
What did you expect?

46:34.370 --> 46:35.140
It was because of the diamonds that

46:35.140 --> 46:36.480
he wanted to enter his office so badly

46:36.480 --> 46:37.680
when earthquake happened.

46:38.160 --> 46:40.100
Right. That explains it.

46:40.990 --> 46:43.900
How much would
these diamonds be worth?

46:43.900 --> 46:45.790
I have a bad feeling about this.

46:45.790 --> 46:47.920
In such case, An unidentified body

46:47.920 --> 46:50.440
would be sent to the police station.

46:50.440 --> 46:53.120
That body must be Mr. Jin.

46:53.700 --> 46:55.750
This is a prelude to lots of paperwork.

46:55.750 --> 46:58.530
I feel like I'll be doing that paperwork.

47:00.990 --> 47:03.860
Where are you going? How much would these be worth?

47:06.550 --> 47:07.720
They don't know anything.

47:27.700 --> 47:30.520
We've looked everywhere but found nothing.

47:30.520 --> 47:32.140
Did you really?

47:37.260 --> 47:39.040
You didn't look through his stomach.

47:41.650 --> 47:42.930
Bring the table.

48:12.780 --> 48:15.120
Put your gun down.

48:15.120 --> 48:17.110
Put your hands up.

48:43.610 --> 48:45.010
Don't move!

48:46.110 --> 48:51.690
If you do... you'll die this time.

48:58.920 --> 49:00.330
Find the target.

49:04.400 --> 49:05.700
The target is unharmed.

49:10.000 --> 49:11.480
Must we leave the others behind?

49:16.990 --> 49:19.300
We're going to

49:19.300 --> 49:21.620
take our bad guy for now.

49:21.620 --> 49:24.530
Alpha Team, retreat immediately!

49:59.950 --> 50:02.170
Do the diamonds  you have belong to Argus?

50:06.100 --> 50:09.410
Diamonds? What diamonds?

50:09.900 --> 50:11.620
I was brought here in my underwear.

50:11.620 --> 50:13.770
I have nothing.

50:18.780 --> 50:19.880
Be honest.

50:20.290 --> 50:23.110
I need to know what price tag Argus has put on your head.

50:23.720 --> 50:25.060
I need to do some math as someone

50:25.060 --> 50:26.690
who should save a jerk like you.

50:29.650 --> 50:33.860
I'm in pain. Get me a doctor! Now!

50:33.860 --> 50:34.930
Your doctor is here.

50:35.680 --> 50:37.880
I think I found what you're looking for.

50:39.370 --> 50:41.990
I don't think you can digest stones.

50:44.890 --> 50:46.140
Did he swallow them?

50:50.370 --> 50:55.140
You jerk, stop pretending that you're sick.

51:02.730 --> 51:06.090
Breathing is shallow and pulse is weak.

51:06.730 --> 51:09.210
I think the diamonds in his stomach have caused internal bleeding.

51:10.460 --> 51:11.640
This is an emergency.

51:11.640 --> 51:13.230
Please get the OR ready for an operation.

51:20.530 --> 51:22.570
I called Dr. Song. Why are you here?

51:22.570 --> 51:23.950
Dr. Song's feeling under the weather,

51:23.950 --> 51:25.190
so I called Lieutenant Yoon.

51:25.190 --> 51:26.880
I'll assist you in his stead.

51:27.990 --> 51:29.350
His BP keeps dropping.

51:29.350 --> 51:30.380
Let's get started.

51:30.380 --> 51:32.200
I'm opening his stomach. Scalpel.

51:37.720 --> 51:38.640
He's bleeding a lot.

51:39.280 --> 51:42.340
By the way, why did he swallow the diamonds?

51:42.340 --> 51:45.490
He did. We're about to see real blood diamonds.

51:46.240 --> 51:48.500
It's a mess. Can you hold it?

51:48.500 --> 51:49.300
Yes.

51:55.760 --> 51:58.750
I'm sorry. I think I cut the wrong blood vessel.

51:58.750 --> 51:59.830
I got it.

52:06.310 --> 52:08.420
It's not a blood vessel

52:09.050 --> 52:11.300
but a tumor on the lymph node.

52:11.300 --> 52:14.000
He's bleeding because of the diamonds,

52:14.410 --> 52:16.380
but what caused the lymphadenectasis?

52:20.470 --> 52:23.910
He was coughing and had trouble breathing...

52:27.100 --> 52:28.410
Everyone! Stop!

52:28.410 --> 52:30.490
Step back from the operating table!

52:30.490 --> 52:31.600
Now!

52:34.350 --> 52:36.500
Coughing, dyspnea, hemorrhage of gastric mucous membrane,

52:36.500 --> 52:38.160
and lymphadenectasis?

52:38.160 --> 52:40.360
By all accounts,

52:40.360 --> 52:42.190
he's showing

52:42.190 --> 52:44.970
symptoms of viral febrile infection.

52:44.970 --> 52:47.910
It looks like pernicious pestilence caused by the M type virus.

52:48.390 --> 52:49.950
Until we know for sure,

52:49.950 --> 52:52.550
we're going to close off this OR.

52:56.700 --> 52:57.570
Everyone except Lieutenant Yoon and me

52:57.570 --> 53:00.100
who have already contaminated

53:00.100 --> 53:01.290
leaves the operating room.

53:01.500 --> 53:02.730
What about the operation?

53:03.950 --> 53:06.110
I guess you and I have to finish it up.

53:14.900 --> 53:16.580
What's the M type virus?

53:17.500 --> 53:19.120
Can you explain it to me?

53:19.120 --> 53:22.930
It's a serious epidemic
monitored by the WHO.

53:23.490 --> 53:25.240
We can find out if it's M2 or M3

53:25.240 --> 53:27.250
through a PCR Test.

53:30.630 --> 53:31.750
What's the difference?

53:32.890 --> 53:36.440
M2 is a little worse than the flu.

53:36.970 --> 53:40.090
M3 is a little better than Ebola.

53:44.520 --> 53:45.590
No! It's dangerous.

53:45.590 --> 53:46.820
You have to speak to them here.

53:47.170 --> 53:48.100
Are you okay?

53:49.030 --> 53:50.390
Are you sick?

53:50.810 --> 53:52.770
It doesn't show that quickly.

53:53.690 --> 53:57.290
We have to wait and see. She's drawing blood.

54:01.540 --> 54:02.860
Yoon Myung Joo.

54:03.350 --> 54:05.630
Still, I'm quite proud of you.

54:06.120 --> 54:08.290
You got here faster

54:08.290 --> 54:09.740
than you received
the package from the flight attendant.

54:09.740 --> 54:11.600
Are you okay?

54:14.660 --> 54:16.930
Wow! Did I scare you, Sergeant Seo Dae Young?

54:23.600 --> 54:24.760
What can I do for you?

54:25.270 --> 54:26.990
What do you want? Say anything.

54:27.690 --> 54:29.080
Anything?

54:29.500 --> 54:32.410
The heart that was drawn on the box...

54:32.410 --> 54:35.160
Who drew it, the one on the right or the left?

54:35.160 --> 54:37.500
The left. She was the one who acted cutesy.

54:37.500 --> 54:41.730
Right. She acted very cutesy.

54:44.520 --> 54:49.250
So you're someone
who gives an answer when I ask.

54:49.560 --> 54:52.380
I don't think this is the time for jokes.

54:54.950 --> 54:57.360
We're dead. We're definitely dead.

54:58.070 --> 55:00.230
They think what we're saying is our will.

55:04.960 --> 55:06.910
Don't look so serious, you two.

55:07.450 --> 55:08.920
We're not going to die.

55:08.920 --> 55:10.640
You won't.

55:10.920 --> 55:12.090
It's ready.

55:12.660 --> 55:14.470
But where can we find a hospital

55:14.470 --> 55:16.530
that can run the PCR test around here?

55:16.530 --> 55:20.980
The general hospital downtown won't be open until tomorrow morning.

55:21.710 --> 55:22.880
There's a pathology lab on the US Army base

55:22.880 --> 55:24.540
20 minutes away from here.

55:25.260 --> 55:26.520
I'm not sure if they'll help us.

55:26.520 --> 55:27.870
I think I can handle it.

55:27.870 --> 55:29.970
I'll get a car ready.

55:48.590 --> 55:49.470
Don't worry.

55:49.470 --> 55:51.700
A virus outbreak is our problem, too.

55:54.460 --> 55:56.600
His BP and pulse are stable.

55:59.040 --> 56:00.860
We've done everything we could as surgeons.

56:05.280 --> 56:06.480
What should we do now?

56:07.360 --> 56:08.970
We need to wait for the results.

56:09.750 --> 56:13.550
The patient's and ours.

56:17.720 --> 56:19.940
The blood samples that you guys gave

56:19.940 --> 56:22.350
is confirmed to be M3 virus.

56:23.970 --> 56:26.030
Are you sure it's M3 virus?

56:26.440 --> 56:28.380
The patient tested positive

56:28.380 --> 56:29.410
and one of the two doctors

56:29.410 --> 56:32.070
also tested positive.

56:33.370 --> 56:37.900
Which one tested positive?

56:47.290 --> 56:50.430
They're really blood diamonds.

56:51.230 --> 56:52.930
They must be real, right?

56:55.250 --> 56:56.600
How much are they worth?

56:58.990 --> 57:00.990
We're the only ones who know how many.

57:02.380 --> 57:03.850
Should we steal one each?

57:05.780 --> 57:07.980
I didn't expect this from you.

57:09.910 --> 57:11.180
You're so smart.

57:36.480 --> 57:37.660
Are you crazy?

57:38.650 --> 57:40.160
Get out!

57:40.160 --> 57:41.690
I'm under quarantine.

58:15.380 --> 58:16.960
It's me, isn't it?

58:44.790 --> 58:48.080
-=Next Episode=-

58:48.080 --> 58:50.840
Her good immune system might harm her.

58:50.840 --> 58:52.380
What should we do now?

58:52.380 --> 58:54.540
It seems that they have found out US Army’s plan

58:54.540 --> 58:56.300
and got hold of our military force.

58:56.300 --> 58:58.300
The situation what we have concerned finally arrived.

58:58.300 --> 58:59.180
Lieutenant Yoon.

58:59.180 --> 59:02.190
The vehicle that was
delivering medicine was hijacked.

59:02.190 --> 59:04.440
Lieutenant Yoon's medicine was there as well.

59:04.440 --> 59:07.380
No matter who stole the drugs, we must caught him.

59:07.790 --> 59:10.540
Where is Dr. Kang? I couldn’t find her.

59:10.540 --> 59:11.920
The local police came yesterday,

59:11.920 --> 59:13.950
And they arrest  Fatima to the police office.

59:13.950 --> 59:15.000
What did you talk just now?

59:15.000 --> 59:17.320
This is Argus, over.

59:17.940 --> 59:19.570
Let’s make a deal.
